revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Elevator_RaiseToNearest}} {{Special|245|tag, speed|Floor and Ceiling}} * ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How fast the elevator moves
Raises the floor and ceiling of the tagged sector so that its floor aligns with the floor of the next higher sector while keeping the same amount of distance between the floor and ceiling.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Elevator_RaiseToNearest: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Boom}} 227:W1 Elevator To Higher Floor || Elevator_RaiseToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Boom}} 228:WR Elevator To Higher Floor || Elevator_RaiseToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 229:S1 Elevator To Higher Floor || Elevator_RaiseToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 230:SR Elevator To Higher Floor || Elevator_RaiseToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
